d the stalwart character of its sparse population. "The translation is excellent, retaining the traditional Norwegian style . . . the tales themselves will also appeal to the interested layman."—Library Journal  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aChristiansen, Reidar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIversen, Pat Shaw.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989z978311066784440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226375205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226375205.jpg  a978-3-11-066784-4  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989c1960d1989  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles